# Prithvi · Muladhara — Cursor Rules
# Read this fully before writing a single line of code.
# Then read SOUL.md. Then read SETUP_LOG.md.

---

## What this is

A sacred healing app. Not a product. Not a wellness SaaS.
A sincere attempt to help people heal the Earth element (Prithvi tattva)
within themselves and on the planet — through mantra chanting, awareness,
and collective resonance.

The standard we are building to: world-class in design, sacred in feeling,
production-grade in engineering. Every screen should feel like it was made
with devotion, not with deadlines.

---

## Navigation — 3 tabs, locked

| Tab | Sanskrit | Purpose | Default? |
|-----|----------|---------|----------|
| Sadhana | साधना | Chanting practice | YES — always opens here |
| Bhumi | भूमि | Collective map (real-time) | No |
| Jnana | ज्ञान | Knowledge (Know) + Journal (Reflect) | No |

Do not add tabs. Do not suggest alternatives. Do not move Sadhana from default.

---

## Tech stack — locked

- **Framework:** Expo ~51 managed workflow + EAS
- **Language:** TypeScript strict mode
- **Navigation:** React Navigation (bottom tabs)
- **Backend:** Supabase (real-time, RLS, anon auth, PostgreSQL)
- **Data fetching:** TanStack Query (React Query) — for Supabase data, caching, loading states
- **Audio:** expo-av, streaming from AWS S3 + CloudFront
- **Fonts:** EB Garamond + Space Mono via expo-google-fonts
- **Animations:** React Native Animated API + Reanimated 2 for complex gestures
- **State:** Context API only (Language, User, Guidance) — no Redux, no Zustand

Do NOT suggest: ejecting Expo, Firebase, Redux Toolkit, NativeWind,
StyleSheet alternatives, or any library adding >100kb without strong reason.

