## Design tokens — never hardcode, always import from src/theme/tokens.ts

```ts
void:      '#0D0A06'   // primary background
deep:      '#151008'
ground:    '#1E1508'
mud:       '#2E2010'
bark:      '#4A3520'
ochre:     '#C17D3C'   // primary accent
gold:      '#D4A843'   // sacred highlights, key numbers
parchment: '#EDE3CF'   // primary text
cream:     '#F5EED8'
ash:       '#7A6A52'   // secondary text
stone:     '#5A4E3A'   // muted / tertiary
muladhara: '#B03020'   // root chakra red — use sparingly
sage:      '#6B7C5E'   // calm green
verified:  '#3A7A4A'   // source tag: peer-reviewed
dharmic:   '#C9962A'   // source tag: scriptural/traditional
observed:  '#8A4A3A'   // source tag: reported/contested
```

Typography: **EB Garamond** for all content/mantra text. **Space Mono** for all
data, stats, timers, source tags. No other fonts, ever.

---

## Proactive flagging — always

If you notice ANY of the following, stop and flag it before implementing:

- A decision that conflicts with SOUL.md principles
- A pattern that could add cognitive load or anxiety to a depleted user
- A library or approach with significant performance cost
- Something that would require a breaking change to existing data schema
- A platform behavior difference (iOS vs Android) that affects the sacred experience
- Anything that touches user data, privacy, or anonymous identity
- A content claim that doesn't have a clear source type (verified/dharmic/observed)
- Security concerns of any kind

Say: "Flagging before continuing: [issue]. My recommendation: [X]. Shall I proceed?"

---

## UX excellence standard

This app is used by people who are often anxious, depleted, or exhausted.
Every interaction must slow the nervous system, not stimulate it.

**Interaction principles:**
- No animations faster than 300ms unless functionally required
- All transitions: fade or gentle slide-from-below — never jarring swipes or pops
- Haptics: only on session start and session end — subtle, deliberate (expo-haptics)
- Every screen usable in 30 seconds OR rewarding over 20 minutes — both valid
- No modals stacking more than one deep
- Loading states must always be present and feel calm (not spinning loaders — soft fades)
- Empty states must feel inviting, not broken ("Your journal is waiting" not "No entries")
- Error states must be gentle and never blame the user

**Scroll and layout:**
- No infinite scroll anywhere in the app
- Lists must have visible end — users should know they've seen everything
- Generous padding — this app should feel spacious, not packed
- Touch targets minimum 44×44pt (Apple HIG) / 48×48dp (Material) — non-negotiable
- Bottom navigation safe area always respected on both platforms

**The breathing circle motif:**
The signature animation of this app. Slow-pulsing concentric rings, 3–6 second
full cycle, easing: ease-in-out. Used around: Earth icon, Muladhara symbol,
mantra player center. Build as a reusable `<BreathingCircle />` component.
Never use this animation for decorative purposes alone.

---

## iOS and Android best practices

**Always handle:**
- `SafeAreaView` / `useSafeAreaInsets` on every screen — notch, home indicator, dynamic island
- Keyboard avoiding behavior on all input screens (journal entry, feedback)
- Android back button / gesture navigation — always test that it does the right thing
- Platform-specific haptic patterns (`expo-haptics` handles this, use it correctly)
- Status bar style: always `light` (dark backgrounds throughout)

**Audio (expo-av) platform specifics:**
- iOS: request audio session category `Playback` so audio continues when screen locks
- Android: acquire WakeLock during active sessions (expo-keep-awake)
- Both: graceful audio interruption handling (phone call, other apps) — pause, don't crash
- Silent mode: Om launch sound and notification sounds must respect device silent mode
- Background audio: Gayatri Mantra must continue when app is backgrounded or screen dims

**Performance targets:**
- App launch to interactive: under 3 seconds on mid-range Android (2020 hardware)
- Tab switch: under 100ms perceived — pre-render adjacent tabs
- Map render (Bhumi): initial paint under 1 second with seed data, live data loads after
- Animation: 60fps target, never drop below 30fps — use `useNativeDriver: true` always
- Memory: no memory leaks from audio sessions — always unload expo-av sounds on unmount

**Accessibility (a11y):**
- Every interactive element has `accessibilityLabel` and `accessibilityRole`
- Mantra text has `accessibilityLanguage` set correctly (Sanskrit/Hindi/English)
- Color contrast: all text meets WCAG AA minimum (4.5:1) against backgrounds
- Audio-only content has text alternative available (mantra text always visible)

---

## Sacred audio/visual design standards

This is not a meditation timer app. The audio-visual experience itself should
induce a sense of the sacred — calm, ancient, grounded, alive.

**Audio standards:**
- Mantra audio must loop seamlessly — no click, no gap at loop point
- Volume: never sudden. Always fade in (1–2 seconds) on session start, fade out on end
- The Om launch sound (see below) sets the tone for the entire session
- Silence is a feature. The silent chanting mode is as sacred as the audio mode.
- Never autoplay audio without user initiating it

**Visual standards:**
- Dark backgrounds (#0D0A06) should feel like depth, not emptiness — use subtle
  radial gradients (expo-linear-gradient) to give them warmth and dimension
- Text on dark: never pure white. Always parchment (#EDE3CF) or cream (#F5EED8)
- Gold (#D4A843) is sacred — use it for the most important element on each screen.
  Not for every button. Not for decoration. For what matters most.
- The Devanagari script for mantra text: large, EB Garamond, generous line height (1.8)
  — let it breathe. Sanskrit should never look cramped.
- Source tags (verified/dharmic/observed): small, Space Mono, subtle — they inform,
  they don't dominate
- Images and icons: minimal. This app communicates through type, light, and sound
  more than through illustration

**The Om launch experience (optional, default ON for new users):**
- On app cold open, before the Sadhana screen appears: a 2–3 second Om sound
  fades in softly, holds briefly, then fades out as the screen fades in
- The screen during this moment: pure #0D0A06 with a single gold breathing circle
  at center — nothing else
- Respects device silent mode: if phone is on silent, skip the sound but show the circle
- Setting: "Om on open" toggle in Settings (Jnana → Reflect → Settings or Profile area)
- Default: ON for first install. User can turn off. Never ask them to turn it back on.
- Audio file: a clean, single Om — not a recording with reverb tail longer than 3 seconds
- This is the app's first impression. It must be the best 3 seconds in the app.

---

## Documentation standards

Every file, component, and function should be self-documenting.

**Components:**
```tsx
/**
 * BreathingCircle
 * Slow-pulsing concentric rings used as the app's signature calming motif.
 * Animation: 3–6 second full cycle, ease-in-out, useNativeDriver: true.
 *
 * @param size - outer diameter in points (default: 120)
 * @param color - ring color (default: tokens.gold)
 * @param rings - number of concentric rings (default: 3)
 */
```

**Data entries in research.ts:**
Every fact object must have: `stat`, `desc`, `source`, `type` (verified/dharmic/observed).
No undocumented fields. No facts without sources.

**Functions:** JSDoc for anything not immediately obvious from the name.

**Complex logic:** Inline comments explaining WHY, not just WHAT.
"// Fade audio before unloading to prevent click artifact" not "// fade audio"

---

## Code quality standards

- **No `any` types** unless truly unavoidable — always with `// TODO: type this properly`
- **No hardcoded strings** visible to users — all text through translation system (en.ts/hi.ts)
- **No hardcoded colors** — always from tokens.ts
- **No magic numbers** — name your constants (`const MALA_COUNT = 108`, not `108`)
- **Component size:** if a component exceeds ~150 lines, consider splitting
- **useEffect cleanup:** always return cleanup function when subscribing to anything
- **Async/await over .then()** — consistent, readable async handling
- **Error boundaries:** wrap major screen sections — a journal crash shouldn't crash the whole app

---

## Content rules — non-negotiable

Every fact, claim, or piece of content in the app carries exactly one source tag:
- `verified` — peer-reviewed, institutional, replicable
- `dharmic` — scriptural, traditional, ancient record
- `observed` — reported, experiential, emerging, or contested

Never present contested research as proven.
Never suppress traditional knowledge because it lacks a citation.
Every new entry in research.ts must include `source` and `type`.

---

## What to NEVER implement

- Streaks that punish absence
- Badges, points, achievement mechanics
- Push notifications except explicit opt-in for global resonance windows
- Social features: likes, comments, follower counts, sharing to external platforms
- Advertising of any kind
- Premium tiers or content gates
- Leaderboards or competitive rankings
- Dark patterns (false urgency, guilt, infinite scroll)
- Solfeggio on the Bhumi map
- "Forecast" language that creates anxiety
- Any feature maximizing time-in-app over wellbeing

